{"kind":"cas-record-v1","metadata":{"entries":[{"origin_package":"github.com/codalotl/codalotl/internal/cli","target_package":"github.com/codalotl/codalotl/internal/subscriptions/openaisub","identifier":"Login","question":"After a successful saved OpenAI subscription login, what public API should a caller use on a later process startup to configure llmmodel provider subscription auth from the saved credentials, if any? Do Login or CheckStatusWithOptions also configure llmmodel.SetProviderSubscription as a side effect?","answer":"There is no exported “startup load” API. For the default auth path, `openaisub` does this automatically in package `init()` via the unexported `loadDefaultProviderSubscription()`: it loads `~/.codalotl/openai_auth.json`, refreshes expired credentials if possible, then syncs `llmmodel` provider subscription auth.\n\nIf a caller wants an explicit public call on startup, use:\n\n`openaisub.CheckStatus(ctx)`\n\nor equivalently:\n\n`openaisub.CheckStatusWithOptions(ctx, openaisub.Options{})`\n\nwith the default path. Besides returning status, it loads/refreshes saved credentials and syncs `llmmodel` for the default auth path.\n\nSide effects:\n\n- `Login(ctx, opts)` does configure `llmmodel.SetProviderSubscription` after a successful login, but only when saving to the default auth path.\n- `CheckStatusWithOptions(ctx, opts)` also configures `llmmodel.SetProviderSubscription` when saved credentials are usable, again only for the default auth path.\n- For alternate `Options.Path`, `syncProviderSubscription` returns without changing `llmmodel`; tests explicitly cover that alternate-path login/status do not change an existing provider subscription.\n- Missing, invalid, expired-unrefreshable, or errored default-path auth can clear OpenAI provider subscription auth via `llmmodel.ClearProviderSubscription`.\n\nSo: default-path saved login is automatically loaded at import/init time; use `CheckStatus` if you need an explicit public refresh/status/sync point. There is no public API in `openaisub` to sync arbitrary non-default saved credentials into `llmmodel`."}]},"additional_info":{"unix_timestamp":1779918362,"paths":["internal/subscriptions/openaisub/SPEC.md","internal/subscriptions/openaisub/openaisub.go","internal/subscriptions/openaisub/openaisub_linux_test.go","internal/subscriptions/openaisub/openaisub_test.go"],"git_clean":false,"git_commit":"2490c4b04a249f0e007f76cb191fbeefd3e9eccc","git_merge_base":"1a69a8f846e92dbf07db54d31e21b6e8ca075282"}}